        "content": "<p>Hi everyone, I've noticed that the definitions in algebra.big_operators don't use <code>disjoint</code> to indicate disjoint sets, instead writing out <code>s₁ ∩ s₂ = ∅</code> (which is slightly incompatible with <code>disjoint</code>, which reduces to <code>s₁ ∩ s₂ ≤ ∅</code>. Is there a reason for this choice?</p>",
        "id": 175983534,
        "sender_full_name": "Anne Baanen",
        "timestamp": 1568796236
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"238446\">@Tim Baanen</span> My guess would be history...</p>",
        "id": 175984276,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1568796922
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I didn't check</p>",
        "id": 175984279,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1568796927
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, I can change it to use <code>disjoint</code> instead. Might be a nice first contribution to mathlib :)</p>",
